Meet Our Team

Management Team




Eugene M. Jordan, II, Esquire, President & CEO
Gene has over 35 years of estate planning and fiduciary law experience. Gene holds a BA from North Carolina Wesleyan College, Certificate of Trust Management and Juris Doctor from Campbell University. He is a current member and past president of the Peninsula Estate Planning Council and a current member of the Hampton Roads Estate Planning Council. Gene serves on the boards of Riverside Regional Medical Center, The Benardine Sisters Foundation, Peninsula Chapter of the Virginia Center for Inclusive Communities, Smart Beginnings of the Virginia Peninsula, and a member of the Hampton Rotary Club.




C. Kay Alligood, Senior Vice President & Chief Administrative Officer
Kay has over 45 years experience in the financial service industry, with 35 of those years in the trust and wealth management sector. She manages the personal trust division and is a graduate of Cannon Trust School and Cannon Personal Trust Advanced Administration School. She is a member of the Peninsula Estate Planning Council.




 
Administration Team




Toni D. Dean, CPA, Vice President & Chief Tax Officer
Toni has over 30 years of experience in tax preparation and tax counseling. She holds a B.A. in accounting from North Carolina State University. As a Certified Public Accountant, her primary focus is on individual and fiduciary taxation. Toni is an honor graduate of Cannon Trust Tax School.




Michelle Whittington, CSOP, Vice President & Trust Operations Officer
Michelle has over 30 years of investment management and trust operations experience. She is a Certified Securities Operations Professional. She attended Cannon Financial Institute and earned her certifications in Trust Securities and Trust Operations. She is a graduate of the Cannon Securities Graduate Program. She has attended various AIB classes and seminars.




 
Business Development Team




Dee Burcher,  Marketing & Development Officer 
Dee has over 30 years of experience in the financial industry. She assists with the business development efforts of the company which include directing the marketing activities of Old Point Trust. Dee also directs company training efforts to increase awareness of company services. She and her family are lifelong residents of the Peninsula.




Investments Team




McKim Williams, Jr., Senior Vice President & Chief Investment Officer 
McKim has over 25 years of investment and portfolio management experience.  In addition to overseeing our investment research and portfolio management, he also writes our Investment Commentary newsletter.   McKim attained both his B.A and M.B.A. from The College of William & Mary and has attained Bloomberg® Certification for both Equity & Fixed Income.   He is Past President of the Rotary Club of Newport News and is a member of the Economics Club of Hampton Roads.  




Bill McLachlan, CFP®, Vice President & Investment Officer
Bill has over 35 years of investment management experience and he is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ professional.   He has a B.S. in Commerce from the University of Virginia and a Certificate in Financial Planning from Virginia Commonwealth University.  He has completed the National Graduate Trust School at Northwestern University and the Southeastern Trust School at Campbell University. 




 
Relationship Managers - Personal Trust Team




S. Patricia Meir, CTFA, Vice President & Relationship Manager
Tricia has over 25 years of experience in the financial services industry, with 20 of those years in the wealth management arena. She graduated with honors from Cannon Trust School and has a B.S. in Finance and a Certified Trust & Financial Advisor designation. Tricia is a member of the Peninsula Estate Planning Council.




Robert T. Cowling, CLU, Vice President & Relationship Manager
Rob has over 35 years experience in the financial services industry. He is a member and Past President of the Peninsula Estate Planning Council and also the Society of Financial Service Professionals-Peninsula Chapter. He is a Graduate of Cannon Trust School, and a Chartered Life Underwriter.




Natalie D. Gill, CTFA, Vice President & Relationship Manager
Natalie has over 15 years of experience in the Trust and Wealth Management industry. She earned her Bachelor of Business Administration and Certificate of Trust Management from Campbell University. Natalie also completed the American Bankers Association National Trust School and National Graduate Trust School and has the Certified Trust and Financial Advisor certification. She is also a member of the Peninsula Estate Planning Council.




Retirement Services Team - Old Point Trust




Kyle W Dunigan, CPC, QPA, QKA, Vice President & Retirement Services Officer
Kyle has over 15 years of experience in the fields of qualified and non-qualified plan administration and consulting. He is an associate member of the America Society of Pension Professionals & Actuaries (ASPPA), and he regularly attends various continuing education seminars sponsored by ASPPA, FIS, and other retirement and fiduciary related organizations.
 




Leesa Barton, Retirement Services Administrator
Leesa joined the Old Point Team in 2015. She has over 10 years of customer service experience and a background in retirement accounts. She is a graduate of Evangel University with a Bachelors Degree in Business Management. She works with Kyle and Roseanna to handle the 401(k) daily record keeping and IRA account administration.





Roseanna Blackham, Retirement Services Specialist
Roseanna has been a part of the Old Point Team for over 20 years. Specializing in the Retirement Services area, she handles all aspects in the recordkeeping of 401(k) plans and Profit Sharing, from inputting the census to producing the 5500's.




 
Penact




Becky J. Nicholas, CPC, Senior Vice President & Managing Director
Becky has over 30 years of experience in the qualified plan area. She is a course instructor for the ASPPA Qualified Pension Administrator's Program, as well as the Retirement Plans course for the Certified Employee Benefit Specialist  Program. She has given numerous presentations to various professional financial and accounting organizations. Becky is an associate member of the American Society of Pension Professionals and Actuaries (ASPPA).




Deborah W. Henry, CPC, ERPA, Vice President 
Debbie brings over 25 years of experience to retirement plan administration. She is an associate member of the American Society of Pension Professionals and Actuaries (ASPPA) and an enrolled Retirement Plan Agent through the IRS. In an effort to keep on the cutting edge of of the industry, Debbie regularly attends various continuing education seminars sponsored by ASPPA and Corbel.




Maureen J. Ringo, CPC, ERPA, Vice President 
Maureen brings over 20 years of service to the team. She is an associate member of the American Society of Pension Professionals and Actuaries (ASPPA) and an enrolled Retirement Plan Agent through the IRS. Maureen helps coordinate plan design, implementation, and education for clients.




 





