Several equities research analysts have recently weighed in on CSCO shares. Deutsche Bank AG reiterated a “buy” rating and issued a $42.00 price target on shares of Cisco Systems in a report on Monday, April 10th. Robert W. Baird reiterated a “buy” rating on shares of Cisco Systems in a report on Monday, May 1st. Vetr downgraded Cisco Systems from a “strong-buy” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $37.03 price target on the stock. in a report on Wednesday, April 26th. Jefferies Group LLC reiterated a “buy” rating and issued a $37.00 price target on shares of Cisco Systems in a report on Wednesday, April 26th. Finally, Drexel Hamilton reiterated a “buy” rating and issued a $40.00 price target on shares of Cisco Systems in a report on Tuesday, May 16th. Twelve research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and twenty-four have given a buy rating to the company’s stock. The stock currently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus price target of $35.32.
