Chicago Equity Partners LLC Sells 75,125 Shares of Philip Morris International Inc (PM)

					Posted by Tristan Rich on Jul 18th, 2017 // No Comments 




Chicago Equity Partners LLC cut its position in  Philip Morris International Inc (NYSE:PM) by 20.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 297,040 shares of the company’s stock after selling 75,125 shares during the period. Philip Morris International comprises approximately  1.0% of Chicago Equity Partners LLC’s holdings, making the stock its 14th largest position. Chicago Equity Partners LLC’s holdings in Philip Morris International were worth $33,536,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
A number of other institutional investors have also recently made changes to their positions in the company. Cedar Rock Capital Ltd. increased its position in shares of  Philip Morris International by 0.5% in the fourth quarter. Cedar Rock Capital Ltd. now owns 11,945,653 shares of the company’s stock worth $1,092,908,000 after buying an additional 58,068 shares in the last quarter.  Gardner Russo & Gardner LLC increased its position in shares of  Philip Morris International by 0.5% in the fourth quarter. Gardner Russo & Gardner LLC now owns 10,363,811 shares of the company’s stock worth $948,185,000 after buying an additional 49,798 shares in the last quarter.  Franklin Resources Inc. increased its position in shares of  Philip Morris International by 16.5% in the fourth quarter. Franklin Resources Inc. now owns 8,753,376 shares of the company’s stock worth $800,847,000 after buying an additional 1,240,300 shares in the last quarter.  Sumitomo Mitsui Trust Holdings Inc. increased its position in shares of  Philip Morris International by 0.4% in the first quarter. Sumitomo Mitsui Trust Holdings Inc. now owns 4,357,568 shares of the company’s stock worth $491,969,000 after buying an additional 18,903 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, DZ BANK AG Deutsche Zentral Genossenschafts Bank Frankfurt am Main purchased a new position in shares of  Philip Morris International during the fourth quarter worth approximately $351,755,000. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  72.31% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Philip Morris International Inc alerts:



Philip Morris International Inc (NYSE PM) opened at 119.00 on Tuesday. Philip Morris International Inc has a one year low of $86.78 and a one year high of $123.55. The company has a 50-day moving average of $118.52 and a 200 day moving average of $107.63. The firm has a market cap of $184.82 billion, a P/E ratio of 26.34 and a beta of 0.94. 




Philip Morris International (NYSE:PM) last released its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, April 20th. The company reported $0.98 EPS for the quarter, missing the consensus estimate of $1.03 by $0.05. The firm had revenue of $6.06 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $6.47 billion. Philip Morris International had a negative return on equity of 65.44% and a net margin of 9.40%. The company’s quarterly revenue was down .3% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period last year, the firm earned $0.98 EPS.  Equities research analysts expect that  Philip Morris International Inc will post $4.90 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Tuesday, July 11th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 23rd were given a dividend of $1.04 per share. This represents a $4.16 annualized dividend and a yield of 3.50%. The ex-dividend date  was Wednesday, June 21st. Philip Morris International’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is 92.04%. 
