OLD Point Trust & Financial Services N A Sells 738 Shares of Coca-Cola Company (The) (KO)


					Posted by Oliver Carreras on Jul 15th, 2017 // No Comments




OLD Point Trust & Financial Services N A lowered its stake in shares of  Coca-Cola Company (The) (NYSE:KO) by 1.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The fund owned 60,036 shares of the company’s stock after selling 738 shares during the period. Coca-Cola Company (The) makes up  approximately  1.5% of OLD Point Trust & Financial Services N A’s investment portfolio, making the stock its 27th largest position. OLD Point Trust & Financial Services N A’s holdings in Coca-Cola Company (The) were worth $2,548,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
A number of other hedge funds have also added to or reduced their stakes in KO. HighPoint Advisor Group LLC raised its stake in  Coca-Cola Company (The) by 10.2% in the third quarter. HighPoint Advisor Group LLC now owns 38,575 shares of the company’s stock worth $1,586,000 after buying an additional 3,567 shares in the last quarter.  Mcmillion Capital Management Inc. raised its stake in  Coca-Cola Company (The) by 5.0% in the third quarter. Mcmillion Capital Management Inc. now owns 43,434 shares of the company’s stock worth $1,838,000 after buying an additional 2,087 shares in the last quarter.  RGT Capital Management Ltd. purchased a new stake in  Coca-Cola Company (The) during the third quarter worth about $4,819,000.  Barnett & Company Inc. raised its stake in  Coca-Cola Company (The) by 27.7% in the third quarter. Barnett & Company Inc. now owns 2,837 shares of the company’s stock worth $120,000 after buying an additional 616 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Sfmg LLC raised its stake in  Coca-Cola Company (The) by 1.9% in the third quarter. Sfmg LLC now owns 11,267 shares of the company’s stock worth $477,000 after buying an additional 207 shares in the last quarter. 63.93% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 


 Get Coca-Cola Company (The) alerts:



Coca-Cola Company (NYSE:KO) traded up 0.56% during midday trading on Friday, reaching $44.68. 8,558,718 shares of the company’s stock traded hands. Coca-Cola Company has a 52-week low of $39.88 and a 52-week high of $46.06. The stock has a 50-day moving average of $44.99 and a 200 day moving average of $42.80. The company has a market cap of $190.90 billion, a P/E ratio of 31.44 and a beta of 0.69. 





Coca-Cola Company (The) (NYSE:KO) last released its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, April 25th. The company reported $0.43 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.44 by $0.01. Coca-Cola Company (The) had a net margin of 15.30% and a return on equity of 33.17%. The firm had revenue of $9.12 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $8.85 billion. During the same period in the prior year, the company earned $0.45 EPS. The business’s quarterly revenue was down 11.3% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, analysts anticipate that  Coca-Cola Company will post $1.89 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Monday, July 3rd. Stockholders of record on Thursday, June 15th were paid a $0.37 dividend. This represents a $1.48 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 3.31%. The ex-dividend date  was Tuesday, June 13th. Coca-Cola Company (The)’s dividend payout ratio  is currently 103.50%. 
